# AI Provider Architecture

`src/lib/ai/` uses a Strategy pattern so the LLM backend can be swapped via a
single env var: `AI_PROVIDER` = `dedalus` | `gemini` | `qwen` | `openai`.

**Current default: `qwen`** — Alibaba DashScope (origin / production on Vercel).

## File Layout

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `types.ts` | Shared interfaces (`AIProvider`, `ProfileInput`, …) + response parsers |
| `prompts.ts` | All prompt templates (shared across providers) |
| `search.ts` | Google Search grounding + PDF extraction via Gemini AI Studio |
| `base-provider.ts` | Abstract base class with default AIProvider implementations |
| `dedalus.ts` | **Dedalus provider** — routes to any model via unified API gateway |
| `gemini.ts` | Gemini provider — extends base, overrides profile gen (native search) |
| `qwen.ts` | Qwen/DashScope provider — extends base, custom image generation |
| `openai.ts` | OpenAI provider — extends base, DALL-E 3 image generation |
| `index.ts` | Registry-based factory + public API re-exports |

## Qwen / DashScope (default)

- `AI_PROVIDER=qwen` (default in `src/lib/env.ts` and factory fallback)
- `DASHSCOPE_API_KEY` — from [DashScope console](https://dashscope.console.aliyun.com/)
- Multimodal + image APIs via `src/lib/ai/qwen.ts`

For Google Search grounding and PDF extraction in qwen mode, configure `GEMINI_API_KEY` or Vertex (`GOOGLE_CLOUD_*`) per `search.ts`.

## Dedalus Provider (optional gateway)

The Dedalus provider uses the [Dedalus Labs](https://dedaluslabs.ai) gateway which provides:
- **Any model via one API**: OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, xAI, DeepSeek, Mistral
- **MCP server support**: connect to hosted tool servers
- **No vendor lock-in**: switch models by changing a string

### Env vars
- `DEDALUS_API_KEY` — API key from Dedalus dashboard
- `DEDALUS_MODEL` — default model for general tasks (e.g. `google/gemini-2.5-flash`)
- `DEDALUS_MATCH_MODEL` — model for expert matching (e.g. `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929`)

### Model selection
- General tasks (profile, writing): fast + cheap model like `google/gemini-2.5-flash`
- Expert matching: stronger model like `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929`
- Image generation: `openai/dall-e-3` via Dedalus
- Can switch models per-task without changing providers

## Key Rule

Prompts live in `prompts.ts`. When changing prompt wording, you update once
and all providers benefit. Never duplicate prompts in provider files.
